
BIP 10 support

Decode and display transaction, in a way that assists human
verification of what they are signing.  MITM mitigation.

Errors are thrown via js exception.  This may be considered ugly,
dumping a lot of information that may obscure one useful nugget.
At a minimum, someone should confirm that cosign exit status is zero
normally, but non-zero when an exception is thrown.

With all parameters optional, optimist module does not appear to
provide a way to service "--help" style requests.

